full_title: It's ok I'm ok by Tate McRae
title: It’s ok I’m ok

description.plain:
This song was originally teased by Tate McRae while performing at the 2024 Lollapalooza on August 3, 2024. She used an iMessage-like visual to depict herself texting her ex’s “New Bitch,” saying that she “can have him anyway.”

Using the same visual, the track was teased again on her Instagram Story on August 22, 2024, continuing the text message thread.

Later that night, during the closing show of her Think Later World Tour’s North American leg, she debuted the track at Madison Square Garden.

After her performance, she posted a TikTok of her and her backup dancers strutting to the sped up version of her new song and dropped the pre-save link.

The music video pays tribute to other projects like Britney Spears‘ “I Wanna Go,” and The Pussycat Dolls’ “When I Grow Up.”

On Vevo’s Vevo Footnotes, Tate McRae reveals that she worked on It’s ok I’m ok last summer (2023) before “THINK LATER” and put it on the shelf. Tate McRae also added

I revisited it again this year as there was always something so speical and catchy.
